Roles & Responsibilities
We are seeking for a Big Data Engineer/Data Architect to join our dynamic data support team. This candidate will be responsible for various professional fields including big data, data warehousing, and data analytics, supporting the company's petabyte-level data services.
Maintain overseas data centers, including ensuring database stability and high availability, as well as stabilizing and optimizing the big data infrastructure;
Responsible for data-driven decision-making for overseas business, including the development and maintenance of real-time and offline metrics, closely collaborating with project teams for decision analysis;
Select and optimize the infrastructure of data centers, and communicate with third-party vendors;
Implement data security and privacy measures to protect sensitive information and ensure compliance with regulatory requirements;
Stay up-to-date with emerging trends and technologies in big data, machine learning, and data engineering, and evaluate their potential impact on our business and technical architecture.

Job Requirements:
Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, or related field;
Strong command of the Linux operating system, with expertise in at least one scripting language such as Shell or Python;
Advanced proficiency in SQL language, coupled with extensive experience in performance tuning;
Expertise in mainstream databases including Oracle, MySQL, Redis, and MongoDB;
Deep familiarity with cloud platforms such as Alibaba Cloud, GCP, and AWS, along with robust troubleshooting skills;
Comprehensive understanding of mainstream big data technologies like Hadoop, Doirs, Starrocks, and Kafka;
Proficient in cloud-based big data solutions on platforms such as Alibaba Cloud, GCP, and AWS, with a proven track record in tuning and troubleshooting;
Proven experience in designing, implementing, and managing big data solutions, including data pipelines, storage systems, and processing frameworks;
Proficiency in both English and Chinese, to facilitate effective communication with Chinese-speaking counterparts.

Roles & Responsibilities
The Head, Data will play a key role in the Digital and Information Technology department, support the Director in developing data analytics and AI strategy and initiatives. He/she will take responsibility in overseeing the development of the IT data analytics platform, managing teams, and ensuring efficient and effective of data to support business decision.

RESPONSIBILITIES
Assist Director in developing and implementing the organization's data analytics and AI strategy in alignment with its business goals and objectives;
Lead, manage and mentors a team of analytics and AI professionals of different backgrounds; promoting collaboration, and ensuring effective communication and coordination;
Identify training and development needs, providing opportunities for skill enhancement and career growth for team members;
Establish data governance policies and procedures to ensure data quality, security and compliance with regulatory requirements, ensure effective data management and utilization;
Manage projects progress, identify and mitigate risks, and resolve any issues or challenges;
Collaborate with business stakeholders, other IT teams and partners, to identify data-driven and AI opportunities and drive business value;
Oversee the design and implementation of data infrastructure, architecture and systems, including data warehouses, data lakes, and business intelligence tools;
Ensure utilization and adoption of developed analytics products by embedding data and insights into digital applications and business processes;
Perform outsourcing management to ensure that contractual obligations are met and projects needs; Manages vendor relationships and ensure vendors fulfill per contract requirements;
Manage IT procurement, evaluate vendor proposals, make recommendations for vendor selection and procurement decisions;
Ensure compliance with applicable laws, regulations and industry standards regarding data privacy, security and IT operations;
Stay current with industry trends, emerging technologies, and best practices in data management and analytics;
Foster positive relationships and effective communication channels;
Brief and train business stakeholders on developed analytics products;
Maintains and updates the quality records according to the standard guidelines on identification, filing, storage, maintenance, and disposition of these records.
Covers duties of fellow colleagues in their absence
Performs any other job related duties as assigned.
REQUIREMENTS
Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in computer science, information systems, statistics, or a related field.
More than 10 years of working experience with at least 3 years in managing team, with track record of managing data analytics projects
Strong understanding of data governance, data quality, data security and regulatory compliance requirements.
Excellent Interpersonal and leadership skills to manage multiple projects at one time with the ability to work in a fast-paced environment
Good knowledge of project management both waterfall and agile include managing contracts, project budgets, work breakdown structures, and systems integration
Proficiency in data technologies and tools, such as SQL, Hadoop, Spark, Python, R, Tableau and machine learning framework
Strong understanding of cloud-based data platform and analytics technologies (e.g Azure data factory, databricks etc)
Familiarity with AI tools and their application in enhancing data insights and user efficiency
Strong strategic thinking and problem solving abilities
Possess healthcare domain knowledge

